<section_header_level_1><loc_61><loc_361><loc_421><loc_369>4 Super-hedging prices' set and Immediate-Profit arbitrage</section_header_level_1>
<text><loc_61><loc_376><loc_466><loc_431>In this section we will address the pricing method adopted in Carassus-Lepinette [6] for vulnerable claims. We call vulnerable claims, any claim H that involves the occurrence random time τ somehow, and hence it is a G T -measurable random variable and is characterized by a pair of F -adapted processes ( C,R ). Here C is the payoff process of the claim and R is the recovery process, while the binding relationship between ( C,R ) and H is dictated by the recovery policy . The rest of this section is divided into two subsections. The first subsection discusses the pricing set of one-step super-hedging prices for vulnerable claims, while the second subsection elaborates the IP arbitrage results.</text>
